body:
Tested on latest SkiaSharp release, on fresh blank UWP app with:

```csharp
var skv = new SkiaSharp.Views.UWP.SKXamlCanvas
{
    HorizontalAlignment = HorizontalAlignment.Stretch,
    VerticalAlignment = VerticalAlignment.Stretch
};
skv.PaintSurface += (_, ea) =>
{
    ea.Surface.Canvas.Clear(SkiaSharp.SKColors.Orange);
};

// Create a Frame to act as the navigation context and navigate to the first page
rootFrame = new Frame
{
    Content = skv
};
```

- Open the UWP app. Task manager shows 25MB used.
- Resize it to fill a 1440p screen It notw takes 700MB. Sometimes this drops back down to 200MB and sometimes it stays in place. 
- When the window is resized to be small again, memory goes down to 400MB.

The numbers are variable and the high memory usage depends on gradual resizing.

I would expect a SkiaSharp view filling a 1440p screen to take 15MB at most (n. of pixels * 4 bytes).
